programme.title: The Great Elephant Tale

programme.title: Secret World of Sound with David Attenborough

programme.title: Secret World of Sound with David Attenborough

programme.title: Secret World of Sound with David Attenborough

programme.desc: Explorer Paul Rose packs his waterproofs and heads for Derwentwater and Borrowdale. programme.title: Lost Land of the Tiger
programme.desc: Following extraordinary rumours of tigers living in the mountains of Bhutan, the expedition shifts to high altitude. Cameraman Gordon Buchanan captures remarkable footage of a snow leopard cub from over 5,000 metres in the air. Along the Tibetan border, explorer Steve Backshall treks to the mystical Tiger Mountain, where he has a very close encounter with the worlds most elusive predator.

programme.title: Lost Land of the Volcano
programme.desc: A team of scientists and filmmakers explores the jungle wilderness of New Guinea. The team are based at the foot of Mount Bosavi, a giant extinct volcano covered in largely unexplored rainforest. With the help of trackers from a remote tribe they aim to search for the animals that live there, and they make amazing finds, including the nest of the worlds smallest parrot, and new types of frogs, geckos and bats.

programme.title: Lost Land of the Volcano
